The paper deals with the application of deep convolutional neural networks for recognizing horses by their iris and periocular features. This involves computer vision techniques and machine learning algorithms, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and biometrics, which are covered in the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
